   it generates. However, there are at least three significant challenges
   associated with measuring word of mouth. First, how does one gather the
   data? Because the information is exchanged in private conversations,
   direct observation traditionally has been difficult. Second, what aspect
   of these conversations should one measure? The third challenge comes
   from the fact that word of mouth is not exogenous. While the mapping
