   relationship marketing activities in the belief that such programs
   bolster their bottom line. In this study, we develop and test a
   conceptual model that links customer-specific relationship marketing
   investments to short-term, customer-specific financial outcomes. Data
   from a matched set of 313 business customers covered by 143 salespeople
   of 34 selling firms indicate that investments in social relationship
   marketing pay off handsomely, financial relationship marketing
   investments do not, and structural relationship marketing investments
