   purchased consumer goods in which the prices affect both the profit per
   visit in the current period and the number of visitors (i.e., store
   traffic) in future periods. We show that optimal category prices in the
   infinite-horizon problem also maximize the closed form sum of a
   geometric series, allowing us to derive meaningful analytical results.
   Modeling the linkage between category prices and future store traffic
   fundamentally changes optimal pricing policy. Optimal pricing must
   balance current profits against future traffic; under general
   conditions, optimal long-run prices are uniformly lower across all
   categories than those that maximize current profits. This result
