   theory or model produces satisfactory predictions and claims further
   that unrealistic assumptions breed good theories. This commentary
   discusses the problems of his argument and presents a very different
   view about the realism of assumptions.
   Assumptions need not be realistic if the only goal of science is
   prediction. However, a major function of theory is also to explain and
   not just to predict. The role of explanation is more important in the
   social sciences because it is far more difficult to produce accurate
